    <string name="faq_a">A:</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_1">There are several reasons. You may check settings as follows:\101. Did you set reminder start &amp; end time appropriately?\102. Have you enabled Water Diary to auto-start on your phone?\103. Have you installed third-party apps like CleanMaster which may prohibit Water Diary running in the background and send notifications?\104. Have you turned off the reminder?\105. Have you set Water Diary to \"Don\'t optimize\" on your phone\'s Battery optimization settings?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_11">You need to tap on menu and select \"Drink History\" from the list of menu options. Inside Drink History you can tap on delete icon against wrong drink log entry.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_12">You need to tap on menu and select \"Settings\" from the list of menu options. Inside Settings, you can change weather by clicking on \"My Profile\".</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_13">You need to tap on menu and select \"Settings\" from the list of menu options. Inside Settings, you can change active / pregnant / breastfeeding status by clicking on \"My Profile\".</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_2">You need to tap on menu and select \"Settings\" from the list of menu options. Inside Settings, You can edit the drink target by clicking on \"My Profile\".</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_3">You need to tap on menu and select \"Settings\" from the list of menu options. Inside Settings, You can edit height and weight by clicking on \"My Profile\".</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_4">There are 2 ways:\101. You can click on the plus icon to add on the drink log.\102. You can also add drink log by clicking on the application widget from android\'s home screen or today\'s widget from iPhone.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_5">You need to tap on menu and select \"Settings\" from the list of menu options. Inside Settings, backup data to your phone.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_6">You need to tap on menu and select \"Settings\" from the list of menu options. Inside Settings, restore data from your phone.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_7">You can click on the change container icon on the top left of the home screen, then tap on your choice of container. You can also add your customized drink.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_8">You can click on the menu and select Drink History then view your drink history.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_9">You can click on the menu and select Drink Report option then view using following 3 options:\101. Weekly Report\102. Monthly Report\103. Yearly Report</string>
